<F_R_OG_BOIL_MEASURED>1.0490000</F_R_OG_BOIL_MEASURED>
<F_R_OG_BOIL_MEASURED_SET>0</F_R_OG_BOIL_MEASURED_SET>
<F_R_OG_MASH_MEASURED>1.0500000</F_R_OG_MASH_MEASURED>
<F_R_OG_MASH_MEASURED_SET>0</F_R_OG_MASH_MEASURED_SET>
<F_R_NOTES>Comedy of errors
 - Forgot the water treatments, so plain Newlands spring water it was.
 - Effectively a 90m mash as I got busy bottling Miss Macclesfield v1.1
 - Mash tun couldn&#39;t hold enough for one batch sparge, so did two.
 - Added the 20m hop addition at 60m, then took it out at 30m, then added it again with the 10m hop addition at 5m. Didn&#39;t seem to help the bitterness, was still hectic on going into primary.
 - Despite new values in BeerSmith the boild off was still more than expected, only got 21l into primary.
 - Forgot to throw in the sugar!

Then
 - Dry hopped after seven days in primary. Left a further 14 days in primary before bottling.</F_R_NOTES>
