<F_G_NOTES>Belgian caramel-style malts. High temperature of germination. Taste development at up to 220&deg;C, intense aroma. Impart caramel-sweet aroma adding golden to rich amber colour to beer. A distinguishing characteristic of all caramel malts is glassiness. This glassy endosperm creates the desirable non-fermentable components that give true caramel malt the ability to contribute mouthfeel, foam, foam retention, and extended beer stability.</F_G_NOTES>
