<Hops><_MOD_>2013-11-29</_MOD_>
<F_H_NAME>J17/63 2013</F_H_NAME>
<F_H_ORIGIN>South Africa</F_H_ORIGIN>
<F_H_TYPE>2</F_H_TYPE>
<F_H_FORM>0</F_H_FORM>
<F_H_ALPHA>12.0000000</F_H_ALPHA>
<F_H_BETA>4.5000000</F_H_BETA>
<F_H_PERCENT>4.7619046</F_H_PERCENT>
<F_H_INVENTORY>2.7513688</F_H_INVENTORY>
<F_H_AMOUNT>0.7054792</F_H_AMOUNT>
<F_H_HSI>15.0000000</F_H_HSI>
<F_H_BOIL_TIME>30.0000000</F_H_BOIL_TIME>
<F_H_DRY_HOP_TIME>0.0000000</F_H_DRY_HOP_TIME>
<F_H_NOTES>Gooseberries, Cassis, Chilli, Gazpacho.

Experimental SAB hop. J17/63 is a day neutral high alpha variety, which requires moderate planting distances and an average of 9-10000 strings and 27-30000 bines per hectare.  Bines are vigorous and perform well on a standard framework. The medium sized cones with an average weight of 0.24g are semi tight, dense and pick very easily.  The cone to leaf ratio is 60:40.  Alpha development is normal.

Because of the excellent alpha acids content and good yields, J17/63 gives a very high alpha acid production per hectare.

Cohumulone 26.5%, Storeability (Pellets) TBC, Isomerisation (Pellets) TBC, Total Oil ml/100g 1.3%, Humulene 21.4%, Caryophyllene 12.8%, Hum/Car Ratio 1.7, Farnesene 4.9, Myrcene 28.4%</F_H_NOTES>
<F_H_IBU_CONTRIB>10.0376682</F_H_IBU_CONTRIB>
<F_ORDER>9</F_ORDER>
<F_H_USE>0</F_H_USE>
<F_H_IN_RECIPE>1</F_H_IN_RECIPE>
<F_H_PRICE>2.8349523</F_H_PRICE>
</Hops>
