<F_H_DRY_HOP_TIME>0.0000000</F_H_DRY_HOP_TIME>
<F_H_NOTES>Fruity, passion fruit and slightly spicy.

Formerly known as US4/78. This locally bred aroma type hop variety was selected specifically for South African conditions.  It is a very vigorous variety requiring wide planting distances.  The medium size cones are slightly spiky, neat and tight with an average cone weight of 0.16g.  The cone to leaf ratio is 80:20.

Cohumulone 16.6-20.2%, Total Oil ml/100g 0.8-1.0%, Humulene 17-26%, Caryophyllene 10-13%, Hum/Car Ratio 2.7 &ndash; 3.4%, Farnesene 0.1-0.4%, Myrcene 20-35%
</F_H_NOTES>
<F_H_IBU_CONTRIB>19.3778268</F_H_IBU_CONTRIB>
<F_ORDER>7</F_ORDER>
<F_H_USE>0</F_H_USE>
