<F_R_NOTES>Authentic to the style in spirit:
 - fermented at ambient temps ~20C (heating only prevented it dropping below 16C)
 - fermented with whatever German lager yeast I could get my hands on
 - hopped with a locally grown descendant of Hallertau (S Aroma)
Original colour and flavour probably came from the extreme decoction of poorly modified locally grown malts. Not a problem for me luckily.

SA National Homebrew Champs 2017 entry: Oct 2017
Scored 31, failed to progress past the first round</F_R_NOTES>
